I think these 1923 photos were part of a plan to re-arrange the traffic congestion in the city and docks in anticipation of the Harbour Bridge.

From <a href="http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/109762738" rel="nofollow">trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/109762738</a> (SMH 5/9/1923 p.11) - 

&quot; ... Day Street below Sussex Street has been opened up and when completed through to Hay Street, will afford great relief to Sussex Street, as it is wide and well graded ... ... &quot;
